 {"id":"bd-jrrw","title":"Implement timer wheel overflow and coalescing","description":"## Overview

Handle edge cases in hierarchical timer wheel: overflow beyond max range and timer coalescing for efficiency.

## Requirements

### Overflow Handling
When a timer exceeds the wheel's range (e.g., 24 hours):
- Option 1: Store in 'far future' list, re-insert when closer
- Option 2: Use larger wheel for long timers
- Option 3: Return error for unreasonable timeouts

Recommended: Option 1 with configurable max duration

```rust
pub struct TimerWheelConfig {
    /// Maximum timer duration the wheel handles directly.
    /// Longer timers go to overflow list.
    pub max_wheel_duration: Duration,

    /// Maximum allowed timer duration (reject longer ones).
    pub max_timer_duration: Duration,
}
```

### Timer Coalescing
Group nearby timers to reduce wakeups:

```rust
pub struct CoalescingConfig {
    /// Timers within this window fire together.
    pub coalesce_window: Duration,

    /// Only coalesce if at least this many timers grouped.
    pub min_group_size: usize,

    /// Enable/disable coalescing.
    pub enabled: bool,
}
```

### Benchmark Baselines
Document expected performance:
- Insert: < 100ns
- Cancel: < 100ns  
- Tick (no expiry): < 50ns
- Tick (with expiry): O(expired timers)

## Acceptance Criteria
1. Overflow list for long-duration timers
2. Configurable coalescing with window parameter
3. Benchmark suite with performance assertions
4. Documentation of overflow/coalescing behavior
5. Tests for edge cases (24h+ timers, many timers same deadline)

## Test Requirements
- Test timer at exactly max duration
- Test timer beyond max duration
- Test coalescing: 100 timers within 1ms window
- Benchmark: 10K timers, measure insert/cancel/tick time
- Test cascading correctness with overflow timers","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"BronzeGrove","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T19:49:32.472470059Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-30T02:22:55.318415515Z","closed_at":"2026-01-30T02:22:55.318343170Z","close_reason":"done","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-jrrw","depends_on_id":"bd-6z7v","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:42Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-js88","title":"Async Filesystem Verification Suite (unit tests, E2E, fault injection)","description":"# Async Filesystem Verification Suite

## Purpose
Comprehensive verification for async filesystem operations (aqy, tokio-fs equivalent) ensuring cancel-safety and data integrity.

## Test Categories

### 1. Unit Tests
- File: open, create, read, write, seek
- File: sync_all, sync_data, set_len
- Directory: create_dir, create_dir_all, remove_dir
- Directory: read_dir, canonicalize
- Metadata: metadata, symlink_metadata
- Permissions: set_permissions
- Links: hard_link, symlink, read_link
- Remove: remove_file, remove_dir_all
- Rename: rename
- Copy: copy

### 2. E2E Scenarios
| Scenario | Verifies |
|----------|----------|
| Read entire file | Basic file I/O |
| Write + sync | Durability semantics |
| Append to file | Concurrent append safety |
| Cancel mid-write | Two-phase write safety |
| Directory traversal | Recursive listing |
| Large file copy | Streaming copy |
| Atomic rename | POSIX rename semantics |
| Temp file workflow | Create, write, rename |

### 3. Fault Injection Tests
- ENOENT: File not found
- EACCES: Permission denied
- ENOSPC: No space left
- EINTR: Interrupted
- Partial write (disk full mid-write)
- Concurrent file access

### 4. Two-Phase Tests
- Reserve write buffer
- Commit on success
- Abort on cancel/error
- No partial writes visible

## Logging Requirements
- File events logged with file paths and handles
- On failure: dump I/O operation state
- Byte counts: read, written, synced

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All file operations have unit tests
- [ ] E2E scenarios pass under lab runtime
- [ ] Fault injection tests verify error handling
- [ ] Two-phase semantics enforced
- [ ] `cargo test fs` passes deterministically

## Verification Commands
```bash
cargo test --package asupersync --lib fs
cargo test --test fs_e2e
```","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"PinkMountain","created_at":"2026-01-22T19:48:45.105825582Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T07:07:18.380959143Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T07:07:18.380894183Z","close_reason":"done","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-js88","depends_on_id":"bd-aqy","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:14Z","created_by":"import"}]}
